@* =============================================================================
   _IMPORTS.RAZOR — Global @using directives for all Razor components

   This file is the Razor equivalent of C#'s global using statements.
   Every @using here applies to ALL .razor files in this folder and all
   subfolders — you don't need to repeat them at the top of each component.

   Think of it as the "header" shared by every component in the project.

   If you create a new service namespace, add it here so components can
   @inject it without a fully qualified name.
   ============================================================================= *@

@using System.Net.Http
@using System.Net.Http.Json
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Routing
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web.Virtualization
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Http
@using Microsoft.JSInterop
@using MyTowerRegistration.Admin
@using MyTowerRegistration.Admin.Layout

@* StrawberryShake runtime types: IOperationResult<T>, IClientError, etc.
   These are the wrapper types the client returns from every ExecuteAsync() call.
   IOperationResult<T> carries both .Data (the typed payload) and .Errors (any
   top-level GraphQL errors). Always check .Errors before accessing .Data. *@
@using StrawberryShake

@* StrawberryShake-generated client types: IMyTowerClient, IGetUsersResult, etc.
   All types that the code generator emits from .graphqlrc.json + *.graphql files
   live in this namespace. Adding it here makes them available in every .razor file
   without a per-page @using directive.

   The generator output lives in obj/berry/ at build time — you won't see these
   files in the project tree, but they are compiled into the assembly. *@
@using MyTowerRegistration.Admin.GraphQL
